Some days it’s Shoreditch House and glam launches ✨✨  but most days it’s @jimmyplaysbass‘ old tracky bottoms  socks AND slippers  mascara shadows under my eyes  never more than 3 inches from a @pawpatrol toy  no bra and a house exploding in plastic and dirty plates 🤣. Some pics are aspirational and shiny  most are just me  taken on my smashed phone  a bit blurry and dull. My life is story of two halves. I’m lucky the ✨shiny✨ stuff exists - it’s fun and fabulous - but actually I love nothing more than being in trackies  with my hair up  bra off and getting sh*t done 👊🏼 Thankfully for every one of the shiny-glam-days  there are 5 stay-at-home-in-trackies days and I’m ok with that. It’s time to make yourself a priority !! Why is there such a huge focus on this January detox period ?? Veganuary  dry January  new year new you back in the gym for one month then not to be seen for the next five months.. bla bla bla .. it’s not sustainable. What are your reasons for it? A quick fix ? Because it’s trending ? 🙅🏽‍♀️ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Your well being and self care should be a priority all year round  month in month out! Yoga is a huge part of my routine and lifestyle  it helps me re-gain clarity and focus as well as building my core strength. Whether I’m practicing on my own or teaching a class  Mio liquid yoga spray helps me to calm  quieten  de stress and re balance. 🧘🏽‍♀️ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ The spray is perfect for pulse points  pillow  yoga mat  car or office and can help promote natural deep sleep and ease tension through its essential oil blend. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ As part of the @mioskincare #mymonthofmio campaign lets try and encourage small changes and consistency rather than unrealistic short lived goals. Whether it’s spending 5 minutes a day doing breathing or taking the stairs instead of the lift  who’s with me ?! 🙏🏽 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ #mioskincare #ad #yogaspray #aromatherapy #essentialoils #wellnessblogger #wellnessjourney #aromantic #livewell #yogagirl #yogisofinstagram #londonyoga #skincare #bodycare #mindset #mindandbody #consistencyiskey #lifestyleguide #wellnessfitness #yogalovers #yogalife #yogabody #yogainspiration #calming #destress

HAPPY THANKSGIVING . We are so thankful to be celebrating with family and friends today. Modern life can be so noisy and chaotic its easy to lose track of all the wonder in our world. Rough housing is my #1 love language. . And not only does it bring me immense joy to throw my kid on the bed and tickle him until he can hardly breathe  it’s also the best opportunity to talk to him about consent. . Earlier this week I was chasing him and he started yelling  through laughter  “Stop  mama!!” and I immediately stopped dead in my tracks. When he looked confused and disappointed and said  “Again mama?” I explained to him that when he tells me to “Stop” I will stop because I respect him and his words. I reminded him  as I do annoyingly often  that games are not fun and they are not okay if not everyone playing feels safe and is having fun. No means no and stop means stop. . He nodded and then said  “Again  Mom?” And the tickle monster reemerged and the fun was back on. We chased and tickled for the next 20 minutes and he never told me to stop again. Boys are smart! (Not creatures who simply cannot help themselves.) . The more we teach our boys how to listen and respect women’s words  the less we’ll need to teach our daughters how to “avoid” sexual assault 🙄. . Parents of boys: This is on us. #believewomen #boymom #boyswillbeboys #whichinmyhomemeans #respect #integrity #courage and #empathy

When we were in Charlotte for pride  we met another family👪 while waiting in a long line for ice cream (worth it b/c @jenisicecreams is 🤯). This kind family listened intently as our boys chattered on about their lives: how they have two homes  how they have 3 dads (their mom recently remarried) and silly less important things like how their dads are YouTubers (they watch other creators on the YouTube kids app so that makes us cool dads in their eyes.) . In another time or place that couple may have felt the need to protect their son from our modern "alternative family." Instead we were made to feel welcome and totally ordinary. . Pride for us means our boys don't have to be ashamed of their family  and we're so grateful that we can live in and visit places where this is our reality. . #charlottesgotalot #clteats #queencity #sponsored

Who says you can’t eat healthy while traveling? The hard part is making the decision to do so. It’s not always easy for me but I try to keep two out of my three meals clean and healthy and then I’ll eat one meal that may not be so clean - that usually means wine🍷dessert🍰etc. For me  it’s all about maintaining healthy balance and enjoying life.  I’ve been on trips where I allowed myself to eat crap all week long and although I didn’t feel guilty when I did  it would take me a full week when I got back to feel good again and not sluggish. It’s not worth it to me to do that anymore but you’ve gotta do what works for you!💗 I’m enjoying my last full day in Denver before we head back to Houston tomorrow. Hope everyone is having a great week! #eathealthy #whatsonmyplate #nourish #eatforhealth #gf #jerf #healthylunch #kalesalad #poweredbyplants #beets

HAPPINESS. Are some people born with it? Maybe. Do some of us struggle for it? Definitely. ⠀ .⠀ Here’s where I stand. Every one of my core values has come from something I struggle with...⠀ • Motherhood/family — infertility ⠀ • Faith — worry + self-doubt ⠀ • Courage — fear of what people think⠀ • Authenticity — trying to be someone else because I wasn’t enough for myself⠀ • Humor — taking myself too seriously⠀ .⠀ These values are like a lantern that light my way. Every time I’m in struggle  it’s because I put my lantern down. Sometimes I have to struggle for a while and work through things before I’m ready to pick the lantern back up again. But every time I use my lantern  I am truly HAPPY. ⠀ .⠀ Do people have to work for their happiness? I sure do. But what about you? Share one thing that makes you truly happy and give me a 💪🏼 if you’ve worked hard to get there. #littlemissfearless #mytruth #thehappynow

Those products that you use everyday...like your face wash  your moisturizer  and your lip balm. Do you know what’s actually in them? Or where they’re made? Or the effects they may have on the planet? _ The answer for most of us is probably no. At least it was for me...until a few years ago.  _ But it doesn’t have to be that way. We have the right to know everything about the products we use and the companies who make them. To ensure that we’re making the right choice  not just for what we need  but for the planet too. _ Take this Skin Warrior Anti-Pollution Repair Cream by @naturallyseriousskin - It’s free of sketchy additives like phthalates  formaldehyde  petroleum (common ingredients in most skin care products). It’s made in a glass jar and packaged in a paper carton that’s FSC certified. Aaannnnnd  it’s made right here in New York  which means: ✅it’s got ingredients I feel comfortable putting on my skin ✅the packaging won’t end up in the landfill after I’m done using it ✅and it has a low carbon footprint 👉🏼All good things _ Soooo...let’s play a little game. Head to your bathroom  pick up a product you use on a regular  and read the back of the package. Do the ingredients look confusing and ambiguous? Where is the product made? And how do you feel about the packaging?  _ Share what you find in the comments below 👇🏼 _ _ _ #sponsored #naturallyserious #zerowasteliving #ecofriendlyproducts #nowaste #consciousconsumer #zerowaste #nontoxic #sustainableliving #ecobeauty #lowimpactmovement #goingzerowaste #lowwaste #lowimpact #carbonfootprint #lesswaste #purchasewithpurpose #zerowastehome #zerowastelifestyle #ingredientsmatter #cleanbeautyrevolution #greenbeautycommunity #yayforearth #ourplanetourhome #zerowastejourney #lowwasteliving #sustainablysourced #sustainablymade #sustainablepackaging #naturalhealthrevolution

When I was little and asked what I wanted to be when I got older  I often said “a mother”. Sometimes I just stare at this sweet girl in disbelief that she is mine....& that I get to spend the rest of my life raising her  loving her and helping her grow. Some people have those “I made it” moments when they land a long desired job or get a promotion of some sort...my “I made it” moment came when she was placed in my arms for the very first time and it often comes back when she smiles back at me or gives me a squeeze around my neck. I am so lucky to be her momma 💕

Supplements: I reached a breaking point today and I cannot contain this rant any longer 🙃 - I have seen more and more talk of supplements on social media recently. A lot of very large accounts  accounts that I respect  accounts that should know better; preaching the use of supplements. And when I talk supplements in this case I’m referring to BCAAs to vitamins to cleanses to all varieties of powders and blends. - The sponsored athletes and the insta stars all talking about what they’re taking. And in turn  influencing us to believe we should be to. We are lead to believe that we are not strong enough  not healthy enough  not balanced enough – and supplements will make all these things possible. - Let's keep it simple ▪ Eat a wide variety of nutritious foods to meet your energy needs. ▪ If you already do this and have further concerns about your health  seek advice from your GP or a specialist. - Please stop using supplements simply because you think you should  or to mask a more serious problem. Eat well  exercise often  seek professional guidance. Stop with the blind following of fitpos. You deserve to be treated as more than just another customer. . . . . #fitspo #health #3dmj #science #nutrition #nutritionpriorities #supplements #supps #fitness #fitnessindustry #weightloss #fatloss #fatlossinspiration #weightlossinspiration #holistichealth #healfromwithin #nourishing #healthyliving #healthylifestyle #iifym #countingmacros #girlswholift #fitnesscommunity #gymshark #gymsharkwomen #energyseamless #diet #dieting

The “Dumpling King of Chicago” 👦🏻👑aka my boss  insisted I make his wife’s recipe for French Toast using the @chateaudumplings bread dumplings. I’m so mad it took me so long to make it.  It was fantastic! Here is the recipe ⁣ ⁣ 👩🏼Tina’s French Toast 👩🏼⁣ ⁣ • 1 Box of Bread Dumplings  Thawed⁣ • 3/4 C of Milk⁣ • 1 T of French Vanilla @coffeemate ⁣ • 2 T of Brown Sugar⁣ • 3 Large Eggs⁣ • 2 t of Cinnamon ⁣ ⁣ ✔️Whisk the ingredients together  soak the bread dumplings in the mixture and pan fry as you would any French Toast. Top with butter  powdered sugar and maple syrup. Prepare to be blown away. These dumplings were made for French Toast! ♥️⁣ ⁣ This is also a great make ahead breakfast. Refrigerate all the leftovers and they reheat quickly for breakfasts on the go!⁣ ⁣ ⁣ #breakfastideas #frenchtoast #frenchtoastrecipe #stuffedfrenchtoast #frenchtoasts #briochefrenchtoast #frenchtoastday #weekendbreakfast #weekendbreakfasts #breakfast #easybreakfast #easybreakfastideas #makeaheadmeals #makeaheadbreakfast #breakfastonthego #fastbreakfast #easymealprep #mealprep #sundaymealprepday #czechfood #czechfoodblogger #czechfoodblog #czechfoodies #breaddumplings #sweetselfie #deliciousfoods #bestfood #bestfoodfeed #bestfoodchicago #recipes ⁣

Some important life lessons from the universe that I’ve re-encountered in these last couple months: 1. Relieve yourself of any relationships or friendships that are draining. You need your good energy. You need it so that you can share it  and you can’t give or share what you lack. You should be able to give from a place of abundance and overflow. If they don’t somehow inspire you  teach you  or push you to be better in the same way that you do for them  evaluate what you’re getting out of the friendship. If the laughs and good times are enough for you  then great. But if it isn’t worth it  do away with it. 2. When the universe tells you to make room  you listen. If you feel an incisive energy that compels you to make space in your life and trust the universe  don’t resist it. Remember that good things fall apart so that better things can fall together  but this can only happen if you make room in your life for these new and better things. 3. Surround yourself with people who uplift you  challenge you  respect you in all circumstances  and are as good as you or better than you at anything - at your craft or any craft  at business  at relationships  at facing fears  anything. Surround yourself with people you can learn from  this is the only way you get better and grow as a human being. That said  I’m eternally thankful for the few people I have who do just that. You guys are some serious keepers. 💪🏽⚡️ Trust the Source and it will provide. 💛 // 📸: @jess.onesto at @femmefair x @peerspace 🎀

Are you spontaneous when it comes to travel? Do you show up without a plan & just go with the flow or do you you have an entire excel sheet full of activities planned?  My biggest travel planning tip would be to leave room for both. For the most part  we showed up to Iceland without a plan. We booked our camper a week ahead of time & had a rough idea of stops we wanted to make along the way. I think balance is important when it comes to planning trips. Leave room for spontaneity but research is important because you could be missing out on some really incredible sights if you have no idea they exist. With a bit of wiggle room  you can pop into a random bar because you hear live music & or hangout with that group of strangers because they invited you to their table to have a drink. These things happened to us in Iceland and our free/nonexistent schedule allowed us the freedom to just go with the flow. At the same time  we had a few “must-dos” that we were sure to make time for. Sometimes we’d ask ourselves if we were spending too much time at one stop or if we should be seeing/doing more but it’s more important to cater your trip your interest & doing what feels right to you. Quality is always more important than quantity.

“Mornings like this one were made for memories.” ― Maggie Stiefvater  Blue Lily  Lily Blue . . I’ve come to realize that the most important beings in my life came to me as complete surprises. ..My now husband asked me to a dance in high school. We were halfway through the night when I realized I’d been nervous because I liked him. I wasn’t expecting it. Not one bit. Eleven years later and sometimes it still surprises and overwhelms me how much I love him. ..Quigley was no different. It might shock you  considering the fact that I am now undeniably a crazy ferret lady  but it was my husband who wanted a ferret. I wasn’t so sure. But the same day we got the go-ahead from our landlord  five years ago today  I found Quigley in a classified ad. Not even an hour later he was on his way home with us. I remember telling him once  because he was two when we got him and he’d had two homes before us  that he would never have to find a new family again. He was ours forever. He was mine. ..He helped people understand ferrets. That they are not rodents. They’re carnivores and they were domesticated to help hunters flush prey from their burrows  so their paws are made like shovels and their sense of smell is incredible. That they do have a scent  but they don’t stink. That ferrets need to be stimulated and challenged because they’re smart and brave and fearless. That they’re kind and silly and ridiculous and curious. That their hearts are so  so big for such small creatures. ..My husband  Quigley  even Diggle; I wasn’t expecting any of them  but they stole my heart. I’ve missed Quigley every day since he’s been gone. I will never forget a moment of those few years where he was mine. My little love: the very best kind of surprise. . . . #thebookferret #books #bookstagram #bookworm #booknerd #bookpets #bookaddict #bookphotography #bibliophile #instabook s #ferret #instaferret #ferretsofinstagram #petsofinstagram #bookstagramfeature #sockstagram #quigley #missyouquigs #adoptionday #birthday #hewouldhavebeenseven

Exercise as a celebration of what your body can do  not as a punishment for what you ate. I spent years Suffering from a misdiagnosed disease that stole my ability to move without severe pain... Brushing my hair was so tough i had to sit down in a chair just to finish. I went through boots off temporary paralysis  so working out was out of the question for almost a decade. One of the first things I did when my disease was put into remission was become a personal fitness trainer. You know what's weird? For the longest time  I did not know how to be at peace with myself. If I made a mistake. If I was alone. If I was overwhelmed. If I was scared. If I was tired. If I was hurt. If I was hungry 🤪😂... But honestly  it's taken me YEARS to teach myself how to not want to control everything. To instead  just take a deep breath in  hold it for a moment  then LET IT GO. One practice that has helped me is #yoga. This purple mat has been with me since 2015. It's been a place to breath  stretch  relax  get uncomfortably sweaty  cry a little and restart a lot. I'm about to hit another "start button" in life. It's not necessarily going to be easy. But it aligns with my bigger life purpose and dreams. So on this rest day  I did a 30-minute #vinyasa flow sesh. And I'm ready. God has prepared me. And He continues to prepare each of us. For the longest time  it was weird trusting The Universe/God. But so much has changed me within one year that I know that's my core. Make time for things that bring you peace  heart center and positive flow. 💜 . . . . . . . . #heartcenter #mindbodysoul #bliss #relaxation #flexibility #recoverymode #positivity #deepbreaths #healthylifestyle #yogi #bodybuilding #loveyourself #yogastudio

“What a waste of a body!” I’ve heard that at least a dozen times in my life. Usually prefaced with “how tall are you?! do you play basketball?!” When I reply with No  that’s the usual response. What a waste. I used to believe it.  As a 6 foot fall teenager who couldn’t make a sports team to save my life (I even heard a swim coach laugh at my attempts) I really didn’t understand WHY I was so big.  Why I took up so much space.  Why I couldn’t get a date because I towered above the opposite sex from 2nd grade on. Fast forward and now I know.  Yes I’m tall and big.  But I am strong.  I am noticeable  which I used to hate but now I see the blessing in being recognized and heard.  I am a large presence in body & mind. I grow babies in a long torso and wrangled in 3 wild little boys at a time and could hold them safe close to me. I can lift furniture with my husband💪🏻 I can see well at all concerts🤘🏻 I can reach all my cabinets👍🏻 Sure I can never be fully submerged in a bubble bath  I can’t lift my hands up in rooms with ceiling fans and I have to do a deep squat in public restrooms to see my face in a mirror BUT I’ve found that taking up space is what I was meant to do. I shared some thoughts on the tall girl’s shopping problems in my stories today that had a huge response of women frustrated with their larger statures so I thought I’d pop in here to tell you you’re just the size you need to be for your purposes in life♡ and I REALLY believe there is beauty in every size. #betterbodylove ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Recipe below of course 😍⬇️. • #charlottecollardPoultry #charlottecollardSpring #charlottecollardRecipes • RECIPE // • Ingredients • - 2 tsp Miso - 2 tsp Soy Sauce - 1 csp Acacia Honey - Black & White Sesame Seeds - 2 Chicken Breast - 4 Small Precooked Beets - 1 Radicchio Salad - Balsamic Vinegar - Olive Oil - Salt • - Mix together the miso  the soy sauce & honey. - Marinate the chicken for 20 minutes then roll it within the sesame seeds. - Put some Olive Oil in a frying pan and cook the marinated chicken. - Prepare the salad  shred and cut the vegetables  mix them together and add some Olive Oil & a bit of salt. You are now ready to serve.
